    id: 53,
    cat: "ai",
    title: "The best robot vacuum deals available ahead of Prime Day",
    summary: "If you&#8217;ve been wanting to buy a robot vacuum but have been put off by how much it can cost to get a good one, now is not a bad time to start looking. Prime Day is next week, but many retailers are offering early deals on several models we&#8217;ve tested from brands like Roborock, [&#8230;]",
    body: "Eufy’s Omni C28 is a great option for smaller spaces. | Photo by Jennifer Pattison Tuohy / The Verge If you&#8217;ve been wanting to buy a robot vacuum but have been put off by how much it can cost to get a good one, now is not a bad time to start looking. Prime Day is next week, but many retailers are offering early deals on several models we&#8217;ve tested from brands like Roborock, Dreame, and Shark.\n\nWhether you&#8217;re looking for a basic robot vacuum that can cut down on the amount of vacuuming you have to do, or a high-end model that can wash and dry its own mop pads and climb over room thresholds, there are deals available across a wide range of price points. There&#8217;s a chance some of these robovacs will get even cheaper next week, or that additional deals will emerge, and we&#8217;ll update this guide accordingly.\n\nHowever, if you&#8217;re shopping for a Father&#8217;s Day gift or simply need a robot vacuum sooner rather than later, these are the best deals we&#8217;ve found so far. Roborock Qrevo Curv 2 Flow Roborock&#8217;s first roller-mop robot vacuum, the Curv 2 Flow, features flagship specs at a mid-range price. Including excellent mopping, a retractable mop cover, 20,000Pa suction, AI-powered obstacle avoidance, and a compact design.\n\nWhere to Buy: $999.99 $849.99 at Amazon $999.99 $849.99 at Best Buy $999.99 $849.99 at Roborock The Roborock Q10 S5 Plus is down to $279.99 ($270 off) at Amazon , which is just $15 shy of its lowest price to date. The Q10 S5 Plus is one of our favorite budget-friendly robot vacuum / mop hybrids , combining good AI-powered obstacle avoidance with automatic carpet detection. It also features a vibrating mop that does a solid job scrubbing hard floors while lifting itself over rugs, and the set includes a self-emptying dock for added convenience.\n\nIt can&#8217;t match the suction power or tall threshold-climbing abilities of pricier models like the Saros 20, but this is a good value under $300. The Tapo RV30 Max is another excellent budget-friendly option that’s on sale for $161.99 ($58 off) at Amazon , which is just $9 more than its all-time low price. The model that includes a self-emptying dock costs just $30 more at Amazon . You don&#8217;t get AI-powered obstacle avoidance with this one, and its 5,200Pa suction isn&#8217;t the most powerful we&#8217;ve seen, but it&#8217;s still a capable cleaning machine with a wide mop pad that performs surprisingly well.\n\nThe RV30 Max also offers excellent lidar-based navigation, support for room-specific cleaning, and Matter compatibility, allowing you to control it through all the major smart home platforms. Roborock Saros 10 Roborock&#8217;s Saros 10 combines powerful 22,000Pa suction with excellent dual spinning mop pads that do a great job tackling dried-on messes. It can also automatically leave its mop pads at the dock before vacuuming carpets.\n\nThe newer Saros 20 offers more powerful suction and can tackle taller thresholds, but the Saros 10 is still a great cleaning machine. Where to Buy: $1599.99 $1099.99 at Best Buy $1599.99 $1299.99 at Roborock Dreame’s X60 Max Ultra is on sale for $1,459.99 ($240 off) at Amazon , which is its second-best price and $100 shy of its all-time low. We highly recommend the Dreame X60 Ultra for homes with lots of carpet, as it combines powerful 35,000Pa suction with dual rubber brushes that excel at lifting hair and debris.\n\nIt can also climb over tall thresholds and thick rugs with ease, while its spinning mop pads do a good job on hard floors and automatically detach when vacuuming carpet. Other highlights include quiet mop washing and drying along with a slim design that can fit under low furniture. Eufy Omni C28 robot vacuum mop The Eufy Omni C28 combines excellent mopping performance with a small self-cleaning dock that&#8217;s well suited for apartments and other smaller spaces.\n\nIt navigates around furniture and into tight areas with ease, while its roller mop does a great job cleaning hard floors. Where to Buy: $799.99 $499.98 at Amazon $799.99 $499.99 at Eufy (with code WS7DV2ZB8S6J) You can pick up the Dreame X60 Max Ultra’s predecessor, the Dreame X50 Ultra , for $899.99 ($700 off) at Amazon , which is $100 more than its best price to date. While its 20,000Pa suction isn&#8217;t quite as powerful as the X60 Ultra&#8217;s and it can&#8217;t tackle especially high thresholds as well, it&#8217;s still an excellent robot vacuum and mop hybrid.\n\nIts edge cleaning also isn&#8217;t quite as effective as the X60 Ultra&#8217;s, but you&#8217;re otherwise getting many of the same features for a lot less. The Dreame L10s Pro Ultra is down to $349.98 when you buy it directly from Dreame with code L10PUXM , matching its best price to date and $950 less than its original launch price in 2024. Despite its age, it still offers a self-cleaning dock that can wash and dry its mop pads, dispense cleaning solution, refill its water tank, and empty its dustbin.\n\nIt also features AI-powered obstacle avoidance. Its 7,000Pa suction is lower than Dreame&#8217;s newer models, and it can&#8217;t climb tall thresholds, but it&#8217;s still a lot of robot vacuum for the price. Ecovacs Deebot X9 Pro Omni The Ecovacs Deebot X9 Pro Omni features an extendable mop that can clean itself, just like its predecessor. However, it also features Ecovacs&#8217; Boosted Large-Airflow Suction Technology, which optimizes the airflow path from intake to exhaust, rather than relying solely on suction power.\n\nWhere to Buy: $1299.99 $499 at Amazon $1299.99 $525.99 at Best Buy $1299.99 $526 at Ecovacs The Shark Navigator Robot Vacuum RV2110 has dropped to $179.99 ($120 off) at Amazon . While we’ve previously seen it go for as low as $129.99, that’s still a notable 40 percent discount on the basic bot. The Navigator uses lidar-based navigation to create a map of your home and is equipped with a brushroll designed to minimize hair tangles.",
    source: "The Verge",
    url: "https://www.theverge.com/gadgets/951081/robot-vacuum-mop-deals-amazon-prime-day-2026",
